---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Editorial Policy" breadcrumbs={[{ name: 'Editorial Policy', path: '/editorial-policy/' }]}>
  <div class="page-shell py-4 sm:py-5">
    <div class="page-main">
      <p class="folio mb-4">Editorial Policy</p>
      <div class="prose-nlu">
        <h2>Source material</h2>
        <p>
          Cover essays and lexicon entries draw on published academic research, primarily SSRN
          working papers by Liang Zhang. They are written for a general readership and are not
          substitutes for the full papers.
        </p>

        <h2>How essays relate to research</h2>
        <p>
          A single working paper may yield several essays when the same argument speaks to
          different readers — for example, a paper on AI latency may inform both a society essay
          on fairness and a life essay on everyday waiting. Each cover essay is one long-form
          reading of a research line, not a summary of an entire paper.
        </p>

        <h2>Adaptation and attribution</h2>
        <p>
          When an essay adapts a specific section of a source paper, the essay footer states the
          source and section. For academic citation, use the original SSRN paper. For general
          reference to an essay on this site, cite the essay URL and publication date.
        </p>

        <h2>Independence</h2>
        <p>
          NLUCloud AI &amp; Society Review is editorially independent. It is not peer-reviewed
          in the journal sense, nor affiliated with an institution. Research papers and cover
          essays serve different audiences and should be cited accordingly.
        </p>

        <h2>Editor&rsquo;s Notes</h2>
        <p>
          Editor&rsquo;s Notes, when published, are signed editorial commentary — synthesis and
          reflection on the magazine&rsquo;s themes. They are clearly labeled and distinct from
          research-derived cover essays.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
